[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is it known if there are some measurable spaces <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span> for which <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mi>E</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X^E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> always exists? Or at least, is it known whether some <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mi>E</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X^E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> exists? e.g. <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span> discrete works afaiu, anything else?</p>",
        "id": 519807512,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1747912294
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What are the measurable sets of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mi>E</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X^E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> when <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span> is uncountably infinite and discrete?</p>",
        "id": 519817544,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1747915589
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is well known that already for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">2^\\mathbb{R}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8452em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">2</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8452em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathbb mtight\">R</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, the evaluation map is not measurable. [<a href=\"http://www.ma.huji.ac.il/raumann/pdf/66.pdf\">Aumann '61</a>]</p>",
        "id": 519832713,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Perrone",
        "timestamp": 1747919755
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It is also known that measurable spaces are monoidal closed, for a different monoidal structure than the cartesian one (giving separately and not jointly measurable functions).<br>\nHowever the Giry monad is not strong for that monoidal structure (the strength on uncountable spaces is not measurable). [<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1612.05939\">Sato '16</a>]</p>",
        "id": 519833343,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Perrone",
        "timestamp": 1747919898
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"277473\">Morgan Rogers (he/him)</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/253118-theory.3A-categorical-probability/topic/exponentiable.20measurable.20spaces/near/519817544\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>What are the measurable sets of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mi>E</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X^E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> when <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>E</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span> is uncountably infinite and discrete?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>If by <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>X</mi><mi>E</mi></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X^E</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8413em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> we mean the product <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>σ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\sigma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">σ</span></span></span></span>-algebra, then it is generated by sets in the form <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∏</mo><mrow><mi>e</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi>E</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\prod_{e\\in E} A_e</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0771em;vertical-align:-0.3271em;\"></span><span class=\"mop\"><span class=\"mop op-symbol small-op\" style=\"position:relative;top:0em;\">∏</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1786em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.4003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">e</span><span class=\"mrel mtight\">∈</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3271em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">e</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>e</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A_e</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">e</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is a measurable subset of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>, and moreover <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>A</mi><mi>e</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A_e=X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">e</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> for all but a countable number of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">e</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 519833954,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Perrone",
        "timestamp": 1747920052
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This failure of exponentiability, similar to what happens with differentiable manifolds, is what leads to <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1701.02547\">quasi-Borel spaces</a>.</p>",
        "id": 519834953,
        "sender_full_name": "Paolo Perrone",
        "timestamp": 1747920292
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alas</p>",
